Australian Seismometers in Schools is a dual purpose seismic network. The program offers both education outreach and provides quality data for monitoring and research. We use Guralp CMG-6TD seismometers and stream data live data to the schools and Geoscience Australia as well as providing the data to IRIS and the Australian AusPass data server. AuSIS infrastructure is supported by AuScope Geophysical Observatory program.
